# Secrets — never commit
.env
.env.*
# Allow specific committed examples (no real secrets)
!companies/concise/.env.local.example
*.pem
*.key
secrets/
**/credentials.json
**/service-account*.json

# Architecture note (2026-05-02):
# This is the local monorepo. ALL files here are tracked in the
# local git repo (no GitHub remote yet — defer until traction).
# CHIEF_OF_STAFF.md, PORTFOLIO_BRIEF.md, briefings/, and shared/ ARE
# committed locally for full version history.
#
# CoS rolling *-cos.md snapshots churn every few minutes; ignore untracked
# copies to keep `git status` usable. Force-add when auditing a specific tick.
briefings/*-cos.md
# When a company hits traction and gets extracted to its own GitHub
# repo, that EXTRACTED repo will NOT include these monorepo-level
# files (they stay only in the local parent monorepo). The extraction
# script (when written) will handle this filtering.
# Paperclip — entire upstream repo is gitignored from our parent repo.
# It has its own .git directory pointing to github.com/paperclipai/paperclip.
# We don't track its source in our repo because it's a third-party dep.
# Anyone setting up AgentCompanies on a fresh machine runs:
#   cd infrastructure && git clone https://github.com/paperclipai/paperclip.git
#   cd paperclip && pnpm install && pnpm dev
infrastructure/paperclip/
# Per-company runtime artifacts (operational logs, transient data)
companies/*/runtime/
companies/*/logs/
companies/*/.cache/
companies/*/site/data/
# Generated content drafts (kept in Supabase Storage, not git)
companies/nt-ministry/content/drafts/
companies/nt-ministry/content/generated/
companies/concise/content/drafts/
# Note: standups/, plans/, deploys/ folders ARE committed
# (they're agent output history, valuable for audit trail)
# Compliance review artifacts ARE committed (audit trail valuable)
# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
